org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.api

Interface Aggregation<P extends Persistable,R,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - input type for the aggregation
    R - result type for the aggregation
    T - data type of the entries for the aggregation
    All Superinterfaces:
    Persistable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AdapterAndIndexBasedAggregation<P,R,T>, CommonIndexAggregation<P,R>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseOptimalVectorAggregation, BoundingBoxAggregation, CommonIndexBoundingBoxAggregation, CommonIndexTimeRangeAggregation, CompositeVectorAggregation, CountAggregation, DataStatisticsAggregation, DistributedRenderAggregation, MergingAggregation, OptimalVectorBoundingBoxAggregation, OptimalVectorTimeRangeAggregation, TimeRangeAggregation, VectorBoundingBoxAggregation, VectorCountAggregation, VectorMathAggregation, VectorMaxAggregation, VectorMinAggregation, VectorSumAggregation, VectorTimeRangeAggregation

    public interface Aggregation<P extends Persistable,R,T>
extends Persistable
    An Aggregation function that mathematically represents any commutative monoid (ie. a function that is both commutative and associative). For some data stores Aggregations will be run distributed on the server within the scope of iterating through the results for maximum efficiency. A third party Aggregation can be used, but if serverside processing is enabled, the third party Aggregation implementation must also be on the server classpath.
